definition: to think/to believe/to suppose/to wish/to want/to miss (feel wistful about the absence of sb or sth)
to (a place)/until (a time)/up to/to go/to arrive/(verb complement denoting completion or result of an action)

sentences.english: It's so obvious, why didn't they have them before?
sentences.chinese: 这就很显而易见，为何之前的人没想到呢？

sentences.english: The Thunderbolt gained fame as the most powerful and actively used American fighter-bomber used extensively for targeting ground installations.
sentences.chinese: 没想到雷电因此成为了美国最著名的战斗轰炸机。

sentences.english: None of them thought of looking at the ricks.
sentences.chinese: 他们谁也没想到要看麦垛一眼。

sentences.english: We didn't really expect it to start raining so at the first pit stop we kept the old tyres.
sentences.chinese: 我们没想到会下雨，所以在一停后没有换胎。

sentences.english: SUSAN: I didn't realize anyone was gonna be out here, I just sorta rolled outta bed.
sentences.chinese: 我没想到外面会有人，我只是裹点什么起了床。

sentences.english: Hi, Bob. Fancy meeting you like this.
sentences.chinese: 嗨，鲍勃，没想到在这遇见你。

sentences.english: When sugar beet growers switched to the new varieties two years ago, they did not expect legal problems.
sentences.chinese: 两年前，甜菜农们换用新品种时并没想到有法律问题。

sentences.english: Why, hello there, little fella. Didn't think I'd see you again.
sentences.chinese: 小伙计你怎么在这里？没想到还能再看到你。

sentences.english: I did not expect these results,” says Suren.
sentences.chinese: 我没想到会是这个结果”，Suren说。

sentences.english: He had never dreamed that the fund of human knowledge bulked so big.
sentences.chinese: 他从没想到人类知识的积蓄竟会如此汗牛充栋。

sentences.english: I didn't expect Ili's natural conditions are so good.
sentences.chinese: 我还真没想到伊犁的自然条件这么好。

sentences.english: She never dreamed the house would be so beautiful.
sentences.chinese: 她做梦也没想到这栋房子会这么漂亮。

sentences.english: As it happens it's been a very profitable non-event.
sentences.chinese: 没想到这件事情成了件很赚钱的小事儿。

sentences.english: He had followed her into the shrubbery with no idea of trying it.
sentences.chinese: 他跟她走进小树林时，并没想到要试一试。

sentences.english: Pippin:I didn't think it world end this way.
sentences.chinese: 没想到我的生命在这儿走到了尽头。

sentences.english: Hsiang didn't expect the magnitude of the effect to be so large.
sentences.chinese: 乡，没想到效果的幅度如此之大。

definition: unexpectedly/to one's surprise/in spite of everything/in that crazy way/actually/to go as far as to
unexpectedly/to one's surprise/go so far as to
unexpected/hard to imagine/it had not occurred to me/who could have thought that
to think (i.e. to take it to be true that ...) (Usually there is an implication that the notion is mistaken – except when expressing one's own current opinion.)
unexpectedly/actually/to go so far as to/indeed
original/originally/at first/it goes without saying/of course
original/former/originally/formerly/at first/so, actually, as it turns out
